Class WorldMap<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • org.openimaj.vis.VisualisationImpl<List<XYPlotVisualisation.LocatedObject<O>>>
              • org.openimaj.vis.general.XYPlotVisualisation<T>
                • org.openimaj.vis.world.WorldMap<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of data to plot on the image
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentListener, ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, EventListener, Accessible, AnimatedVisualisationListener, AnimatedVisualisationProvider, Visualisation<List<XYPlotVisualisation.LocatedObject<T>>>, VisualisationImageProvider

    public class WorldMap<T>
extends XYPlotVisualisation<T>
implements AnimatedVisualisationProvider
    Draws a world map visualisation as an XY plot. The XY coordinates are scaled to be equal to longitude and latitude.
    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk), David Dupplaw (dpd@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
    Created:
    11 Jun 2013
